r%20edge%20in%20one%20area%3A%20their%20social%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Survey%20Center%20on%20American%20Life%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nonprofit%20organization%20backed%20by%20the%20right-wing%20think%20tank%20the%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%20%E2%80%94%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americansurveycenter.org%2Fresearch%2Fdisconnected-places-and-spaces%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%20based%20on%20a%20survey%20of%20more%20than%206%2C500%20US%20adults%20conducted%20in%20March%20and%20April.%20The%20respondents%20were%20asked%20about%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-antiaging-friendship-social-interaction-relationships-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20interactions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20participation%20in%20their%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20found%20that%2024%25%20of%20non-college-educated%20Americans%20had%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eno%20close%20friends%20and%2017%25%20had%20at%20least%20six%20close%20friends.%20Among%20Americans%20with%20at%20least%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%2C%2045%25%20had%20at%20least%20six%20close%20friends%2C%20and%2010%25%20had%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuestion%20after%20question%2C%20the%20same%20social%20divide%20continued%20to%20emerge%20in%20the%20survey.%20For%20example%2C%20compared%20to%20Americans%20without%20a%20degree%2C%20college%20graduates%20were%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20they%20had%20friends%20who%20could%20help%20them%20move%2C%20give%20them%20a%20ride%2C%20take%20them%20to%20a%20doctor's%20appointment%2C%20or%20offer%20them%20a%20place%20to%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eall%20education%20levels%2C%20Americans%20reported%20having%20significantly%20fewer%20friends%20than%20they%20did%20in%20a%20similar%20Gallup%20survey%20conducted%20in%201990%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Survey%20Center%20report.%20However%2C%20the%20widespread%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhanging-out-book-sheila-liming-social-isolation-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecline%20in%20socialization%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20decades%20has%20been%20steeper%20for%20people%20without%20a%20college%20degree.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F6clGL%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22What%20close%20friendships%20look%20like%20by%20educational%20attainment%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22424%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmericans%20with%20fewer%20years%20of%20formal%20education%20participate%20less%20often%20in%20community%20life%2C%20are%20less%20civically%20active%2C%20have%20fewer%20close%20friends%2C%20and%20have%20less%20social%20support%20than%20those%20with%20four-year%20college%20degrees%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIncreasingly%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20cultivate%20strong%20social%20support%20is%20a%20privilege%20reserved%20for%20the%20college-educated%2C%20rather%20than%20an%20ordinary%20feature%20of%20American%20life%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethey%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Survey%20Center%20report%20provides%20additional%20evidence%20for%20something%20several%20experts%20have%20been%20saying%20in%20recent%20years%3A%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeath-casual-fringe-friendships-gen-z-sad-jobs-alone-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earen't%20making%20friends%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20they%20used%20to%20and%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweekends-feel-different-post-pandemic-isolation-loneliness-economy-tiktokers-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espending%20more%20time%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20year%2C%20US%20Surgeon%20Gene