0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-nones-more-americans-religiously-unaffiliated-who-are-they-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplace%20of%20worship%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20decline%20has%20been%20much%20steeper%20for%20Americans%20with%20lower%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Survey%20Center%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20non-college-educated%20Americans%20were%20also%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20members%20of%20nonreligious%20community%20groups%20like%20hobby%20or%20activity%20groups%2C%20community%20groups%20or%20neighborhood%20associations%2C%20and%20sports%20leagues%20or%20workout%20groups.%20In%20recent%20decades%2C%20Americans%20with%20degrees%20have%20continued%20to%20join%20these%20groups%20at%20%26quot%3Brelatively%20high%26quot%3B%20rates%2C%20while%20those%20without%20degrees%20have%20become%20%26quot%3Bincreasingly%20unattached%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20all%20of%20these%20things%20start%20to%20come%20together%2C%20you're%20seeing%20the%20bottom%20fallout%20of%20these%20institutions%20that%20historically%20have%20provided%20a%20grounding%20of%20participation%20and%20connection%20in%20American%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Sam%20Pressler%2C%20coauthor%20of%20the%20report%20and%20practitioner%20fellow%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Virginia's%20Karsh%20Institute%20of%20Democracy%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Pressler%20said%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bpay%20to%20play%26quot%3B%20system%20in%20many%20Americans'%20social%20lives.%20Public%20spaces%20that%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20foster%20social%20connections%20often%20come%20with%20a%20financial%20cost%2C%20and%20this%20can%20benefit%20college%20graduates%2C%20who%20tend%20to%20earn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Femp%2Fchart-unemployment-earnings-education.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20wages%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-men-working-less-no-college-degree-student-loan-debt-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20without%20degrees%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20go%20to%20a%20coffee%20shop%20or%20you%20go%20to%20a%20bar%20or%20a%20restaurant%2C%20those%20things%20have%20dollar%20signs%20attached%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20go%20and%20join%20a%20gym%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20Equinox%20or%20even%20the%20YMCA%2C%20that%20costs%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20free%20public%20spaces%20like%20libraries%2C%20community%20centers%2C%20and%20parks%2C%20the%20survey%20found%20that%20non-college-educated%20Americans%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20use%20them%20as%20a%20social%20gathering%20place.%20Pressler%20said%20one%20explanation%20for%20this%20could%20be%20that%20Americans%20with%20degrees%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20live%20in%20areas%20with%20extensive%20and%20high-quality%20public%20spaces%20and%20community%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20out%20of%20those%20traditional%20structures%2C%20you%20have%20to%20do%20so%20much%20more%20work%20to%20schedule%20time%20with%20friends%2C%20to%20build%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20the%20work%20gets%20put%20onto%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20people%20without%20a%20college%20degree%20may%20also%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-recommendations-jobs-to-try-this-year-concerts-surveys-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20multiple%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20have%20roles%20with%20unpredictable%20hours%2C%20Pressler%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20he%20pointed%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-economy-trends-workers-delivery-ride-hailing-apps-uber-doordash-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erise%20of%20gig%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years.%20Driving%20during%20nights%20and%20weekends%20%E2%80%94%20prime%20social%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20the%20most%20profitable%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-uber-and-lyft-driver-who-only-drives-at-night-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%20or%20Lyft%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%20who's%20looking%20to%20earn%20some%20extra%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20your%20schedule%20is%20going%20to%20be%20in%20a%20week%20or%20two%20weeks%20if%20you%20are%20working%20several%20jobs%2C%20it's%20very%20hard%20to%20imagine%20being%20able%20to%20plan%20to%20participate%20in%20community%20or%20spend%20time%20with%20family%20and%20build%20those%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20Pressler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20people%2C%20the%20workplace%20can%20provide%20another%20opportunity%20to%20make%20friends.%20In%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-working-from-home-office-misses-friends-loneliness-remote-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%20half%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20respondents%20told%20the%20Survey%20Center%20that%20they'd%20met%20a%20close%20friend%20through%20their%20work%20or%20a%20spouse's%20work.%20However%2C%20college%20graduates%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20done%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fcf4dc4-64b7-407d-b2ef-24e5ba206c58%5C%22%3EGoing%20to%20college%20can%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bsupercharger%20of%20relationships%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20some%20of%20the%20social%20benefits%20of%20a%20college%20degree%20date%20back%20to%20the%20connections%20fostered%20on%20campuses.%20Pressler%20said%20the%20college%20experience%20can%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bsupercharger%20of%20relationships%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20people%20who%20don't%20pursue%20a%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20and%20go%20straight%20into%20the%20workforce%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20may%20not%20have%20the%20same%20social%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20students%20graduate%2C%20many%20of%20them%20move%20to%20cities%20where%20they%20can%20continue%20to%20build%20upon%20their%20college%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20potentially%20the%20leisure%20time%20and%20the%20discretionary%20income%20to%20participate%20in%20community%20life%20with%20other%20people%20who%20have%20college%20degrees%20and%20you're%20also%20involved%20and%20meshed%20in%20these%20networks%20of%20your%20fellow%20alum%2C%26quot%3B%20Pressler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20whole%2C%20Pressler%20said%20that%20he%20thinks%20the%20financial%20and%20social%20benefits%20of%20a%20college%20degree%20have%20increased%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20decline%20in%20some%20middle-class%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20driven%20by%20factors%20that%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-men-working-less-recessions-employment-productivity-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobalization%20and%20recessions%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20is%20partly%20responsible%20for%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20young%20people%20decide%20whether%20to%20go%20to%20college%2C%20Pressler%20said%20he%20thinks%20many%20of%20them%20place%20significant%20value%20on%20the%20social%20benefits%20that%20can%20come%20with%20a%20college%20education.%20He%20said%20this%20is%20among%20the%20reasons%20many%20colleges'%20recruiting%20efforts%20%E2%80%94%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20attract%20students%20%E2%80%94%20emphasize%20the%20clubs%2C%20Greek%20life%2C%20and%20sports%20on%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20the%20social%20benefits%2C%20Pressler%20said%20this%20doesn't%20mean%20a%20college%20degree%20is%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20the%20answer%20is%20to%20necessarily%20get%20more%20young%20adults%20to%20go%20to%20college%20because%20of%20the%20adverse%20social%20consequences%20that%20we%20highlighted%20in%20our%20report%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BRather%2C%20we%20should%20be%20aiming%20to%20mitigate%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20ideally%2C%20eliminate%20%E2%80%94%20the%20educational%20divide%20in%20civic%20life.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20Pressler%20said%20there%20is%20no%20%26quot%3Bsilver%20bullet%26quot%3B%20solution%20for%20Americans'%20overall%20friendship%20decline%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20larger%20decline%20for%20people%20without%20degrees%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20there%20are%20several%20solutions%20worth%20considering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20he%20said%20housing%20and%20neighborhood%20policies%20could%20be%20better%20used%20to%20promote%20connection%20in%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20could%20include%20everything%20from%20housing%20policies%20that%20promote%20more%20middle%20and%20social%20housing%2C%20to%20neighborhood%20policies%20that%20provide%20micro-grants%20for%20block%20parties%2C%20community%20dinners%2C%20sports%20leagues%2C%20and%20block%20clean-ups%20that%20bring%20neighbors%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDid%20you%20go%20to%20college%20in%20large%20part%20for%20the%20expected%20social%20benefits%3F%20Are%20you%20willing%20to%20share%20your%20story%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-graduates-more-likely-have-friends-participate-community-civil-engagement-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728205622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc170075c877a99b6231c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-graduates-more-likely-have-friends-participate-community-civil-e