3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-august-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-rate-cuts-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflation%20is%20slowing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20Anthony%20Saglimbene%2C%20the%20chief%20market%20strategist%20at%20Ameriprise%20Financial.%20He's%20also%20keeping%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20signs%20about%20the%20strength%20of%20consumer%20spending%2C%20or%20lack%20thereof%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-wage-growth-investing-strategy-stocks-to-buy-goldman-sachs-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20wage%20growth%20dissipates%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20pricing%20power%20%E2%80%94%20not%20only%20in%20technology%2C%20but%20across%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20services%20and%20goods%20sides%20of%20the%20equation%2C%26quot%3B%20Saglimbene%20said.%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20hold%20profit%20margins%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20maybe%20your%20costs%20are%20becoming%20more%20stable%2C%20but%20demand%20is%20starting%20to%20slow%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemand%20is%20either%20softening%20or%20steadfast%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20perspective.%20Joe%20Quinlan%20%E2%80%94%20who's%20head%20of%20markets%20strategy%20at%20Merrill%20and%20Private%20Bank%2C%20Bank%20of%20America%20%E2%80%94%20recently%20remarked%20that%20there's%20a%20strikingly%20wide%20gap%20between%20high-income%20households%20and%20those%20who%20aren't%20well%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategy%20chief%20recently%20wrote%20that%20a%20mere%204.4%25%20of%20US%20households%20make%20up%2015%25%20of%20personal%20consumption%2C%20which%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FDPCERE1Q156NBEA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebackbone%20of%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20rich%20are%20disproportionately%20driving%20economic%20growth%20because%20of%20the%20wealth%20effect%2C%20which%20means%20they're%20confident%20since%20stocks%20are%20rising.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Quinlan%20noted%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F266807%2Fpercentage-americans-owns-stock.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroughly%2040%25%20of%20US%20households%20don't%20own%20stocks%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20the%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lower-income%20households%20%E2%80%94%20definitely%20feeling%20the%20squeeze%20of%20higher%20prices.%20I%20know%20inflation%20has%20come%20down%20when%20we%20look%20at%20the%20metrics%2C%20but%20prices%20for%20food%2C%20rent%2C%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20still%20elevated%2C%26quot%3B%20Quinlan%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20is%20limiting%20disposable%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20weakness%20among%20lower-income%20households%20is%20troubling%2C%20strategists%20don't%20think%20it%20will%20show%20up%20in%20corporate%20earnings%20since%20consumers%20broadly%20are%20holding%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20consumer%20is%20pretty%20healthy%2C%26quot%3B%20Reynolds%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20maybe%20some%20warning%20signs%20on%20the%20margin%20on%20credit-card%20balances%20and%20delinquencies%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20not%20enough%20to%20break%20the%20camel's%20back%20on%20earnings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e9ed5200-3a27-426c-b63a-a65a628a84e6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20earnings%20will%20thrive%20in%202025%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20investors%20have%20only%20seen%20about%20half%20of%202024%20earnings%2C%20which%20are%20on%20track%20to%20rise%2010%25%2C%20it's%20already%20time%20to%20look%20to%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20year%20continues%2C%20I%20do%20think%20it's%20not%20about%20earnings%20for%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20trajectory%20of%20earnings%20for%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Andrew%20Slimmon%2C%20a%20lead%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20Morgan%20Stanley%20Investment%20Management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221424%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Factset%202024%20earnings%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fefdcda7031864927f5ad8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22822%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFactset%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20profits%20should%20stay%20strong%20and%20can%20potentially%20improve%2C%20strategists%20say%2C%20provided%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20doesn't%20slow%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20macroeconomic%20picture%20holds%20together%2C%20there's%20an%20expectation%20that%20we%20should%20see%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20re-acceleration%20in%20earnings%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jim%20Baird%2C%20chief%20investment%20officer%20at%20Plante%20Moran%20Financial%20Advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuinlan%20agrees%20and%20predicted%20that%20%26quot%3Bearnings%20will%20reflect%20the%20dynamic%20and%20resiliency%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20that%20we%20just%20closed%20the%20quarter%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Smith%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20growth%20equity%20team%20at%20Allspring%20Global%20Investments%2C%20said%20his%20research%20also%20indicates%20that%20companies%20are%20healthy%2C%20at%20least%20compared%20to%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20talk%20to%20our%20companies%20quite%20frequently%20and%20do%20our%20own%20work%20talking%20to%20their%20customers%20and%20suppliers%2C%20and%20we%20really%20feel%20like%20there%20are%20still%20some%20pockets%20of%20strong%20demand%20through%20our%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20if%20economic%20growth%20comes%20in%20light%2C%20corporate%20earnings%20won't%20necessarily%20suffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20always%20a%20one-for-one%20relationship%20between%20economic%20growth%20and%20earnings%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Reynolds%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20still%20see%20earnings%20growth%20at%20a%20pretty%20robust%20level%2C%20even%20if%20economic%20growth%20moderates%2