%20is%20taking%20on%20a%20campaign%20to%20install%20thousands%20of%20surveillance%20cameras%20across%20the%20city%20to%20ramp%20up%20their%20crime-fighting%20capabilities.%20The%20Chinese%20city%2C%20consistently%20ranked%20among%20the%20world's%20safest%2C%20plans%20to%20introduce%20facial%20recognition%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%20tools%20to%20enhance%20law%20enforcement.%20Critics%2C%20however%2C%20warn%20that%20this%20could%20come%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20privacy%20and%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHong%20Kong%20has%20close%20to%2055%2C000%C2%A0public%20CCTV%20cameras%2C%20with%20plans%20to%20add%202%2C000%20more%20this%20year%2C%20announced%20security%20Chief%20Chris%20Tang%20in%20July.%20The%20police%20force%20is%20considering%20equipping%20these%20cameras%20with%20facial%20recognition%20technology%20and%20AI%20tools%20to%20help%20identify%20suspects.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20police%20will%20definitely%20comply%20with%20relevant%20laws%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20force%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F10%2F05%2Fasia%2Fhong-kong-police-cameras-facial-recognition-intl-hnk-dst%2Findex.html%C2%A0%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20details%20on%20when%20these%20technologies%20might%20be%20deployed%20remain%20vague.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20are%20raising%20alarms%20about%20the%20repressive%20potential%20of%20surveillance%20technology%2C%20especially%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%20They%20draw%20parallels%20to%20mainland%20China's%20extensive%20surveillance%20systems%2C%20highlighting%20the%20heightened%20concern%20in%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20where%20political%20dissent%20has%20been%20severely%20limited%20since%20the%20national%20security%20law%20was%20introduced%20after%20the%202019%20anti-government%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHong%20Kong%20already%20has%20more%20than%2054%2C500%20public%20CCTV%20cameras%2C%20equating%20to%20about%20seven%20cameras%20per%201%2C000%20people.%20That%20number%20puts%20it%20on%20par%20with%20major%20cities%20like%20New%20York%2C%20though%20far%20behind%20China's%20urban%20centres%2C%20where%20an%20average%20of%20440%20cameras%20per%201%2C000%20people%20is%20commonplace.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Tang%20highlighted%20that%20countries%20like%20the%20UK%20have%20also%20started%20using%20facial%20recognition%20cameras.%20However%2C%20experts%20warn%20that%20even%20in%20these%20democracies%2C%20the%20implementation%20of%20such%20technology%20has%20raised%20significant%20concerns%20about%20privacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormann%20Witzleb%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Chinese%20University%20of%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt's%20important%20to%20design%20guidelines%20for%20those%20systems%20that%20take%20proper%20recognition%20of%20the%20potential%20benefits%20that%20they%20have%2C%20but%20that%20also%20acknowledge%20they're%20not%20foolproof%2C%20and%20that%20they%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20interfere%20with%20(people's)%20rights%20in%20serious%20ways%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESteve%20Tsang%2C%20director%20of%20the%20SOAS%20China%20Institute%2C%20warned%20that%20the%20new%20cameras%20could%20be%20used%20for%20political%20repression%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20fighting%20crime.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20further%20step%20in%20making%20Hong%20Kong%20law%20enforcement%20closer%20to%20how%20it%20is%20done%20on%20the%20Chinese%20mainland%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamantha%20Hoffman%2C%20a%20nonresident%20fellow%20at%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Asian%20Research%2C%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20difference%20is%20how%20the%20technology%20is%20being%20used.%E2%80%9D%20While%20Western%20democracies%20face%20their%20challenges%20with%20surveillance%20technology%2C%20she%20argues%20that%20the%20situation%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20is%20fundamentally%20different%20due%20to%20the%20legal%20framework%20supporting%20the%20government's%20authority.%20She%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20feel%20like%20you're%20being%20monitored%2C%20that%20affects%20your%20behaviour%20and%20your%20feelings%20of%20freedom%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20CNN.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728195180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Flctp5q3o_hong-kong_625x300_25_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fthis-city-is-expanding-its-cctv-network-despite-being-among-safest-6727374%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hong%20Kong's%20police%20force%20is%20taking%20on%20a%20campaign%20to%20install%20thousands%20of%20surveillance%20cameras%20across%20the%20city%20to%20ramp%20up%20their%20crime-fighting%20capabilities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fthis-city-is-expanding-its-cctv-network-despite-being-among-safest-6727374%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IndiGo%20OTP%20crash%20saw%20lowest%20punctuality%20among%20all%20airlines%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728195020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113980426%2Cimgsize-212746.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Foutage-impact-indigo-otp-crashed-on-saturday-saw-lowest-punctuality-among-all-airlines%2Farticleshow%2F113980412.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22IndiGo's%20daily%20operations%20were%20severely%20disrupted%20on%20Saturday%20due%20to%20a%20significant%20system%20outage%2C%20reducing%20on-time%20performance%20to%2054%25.%20The%20outage%20caused%20long%20queues%2C%20manual%20boarding%20pass%20issuance%2C%20and%20significant%20delays%2C%20impacting%203%20lakh%20passengers.%20The%20DGCA%20has%20requested%20a%20detailed%20report%20to%20prevent%20future%20recurrences.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22SAURABH%20SINHA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2250%20stu