%20mid-2022%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Redfin.%20The%20decline%20is%20an%20outlier%20compared%20to%20the%20broader%20US%20housing%20market%2C%20which%20is%20still%20prices%20hovering%20around%20record%20highs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20homes%20for%20sale%20in%20Texas%20were%20being%20scooped%20up%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20days%2C%20but%20it's%20now%20taking%20months%20for%20sellers%20to%20find%20a%20buyer%2C%20according%20to%20James%20Willoughby%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%20based%20in%20Austin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20instances%2C%20Willoughby%20says%20he's%20encouraged%20sellers%20to%20slash%20prices%20by%2020%25-30%25.%20According%20to%20Redfin%2C%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redfin.com%2Fstate%2FTexas%2Fhousing-market%23demand%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomes%20in%20Texas%20saw%20a%20price%20drop%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20such%20an%20avalanche%20of%20buyers%20moving%20here%20from%20elsewhere%20and%20not%20that%20many%20people%20selling.%20That's%20how%20we%20got%20into%20the%20craziness%20that%20we%20got%20into%20several%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20Texas%20housing%20market%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20adding%20that%20he's%20seen%20a%20%26quot%3Bfair%20amount%20of%20people%26quot%3B%20looking%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20state%20in%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Wheeler%2C%20an%20Amarillo-based%20real-estate%20agent%2C%20says%20the%20number%20of%20clients%20who%20are%20looking%20to%20move%20out%20of%20Texas%20is%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20equal%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20number%20of%20clients%20looking%20to%20move%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20price%20reductions%2C%20more%20price%20reductions%20than%20normal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrice%20cuts%20suggest%20that%20housing%20markets%20like%20Austin%20and%20Dallas%20are%20likely%20approaching%20a%20bottom%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin's%20chief%20economist%20Daryl%20Fairweather%2C%20though%20she%20noted%20that%20the%20trend%20wasn't%20uniform%20across%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20boom%20cycle's%20kind%20of%20coming%20to%20a%20close%2C%26quot%3B%20Fairweather%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d645e44-b331-4da0-b652-00cbb2fbcaea%5C%22%3EWaning%20affordability%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20pandemic%20struck%2C%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-texas-pandemic-migration-boom-sunbelt-austin-housing-crisis-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflocked%20to%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20search%20of%20cheaper%20living%20relative%20to%20other%20metropolitan%20areas%2C%20Fairweather%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20agents%20say%20they're%20seeing%20prices%20come%20down%20faster%20than%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20they're%20also%20coming%20down%20from%20a%20higher%20peak%20after%20the%20housing%20feeding%20frenzy%20that%20took%20place%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202020%2C%20the%20median%20home%20price%20in%20Texas%20was%20%24253%2C600%2C%20around%2020%25%20lower%20than%20the%20national%20median%20of%20%24303%2C577%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20home%20prices%20in%20Texas%20have%20shot%20up%2037%25%2C%20with%20the%20median%20price%20clocking%20in%20at%20%24348%2C300%20in%20August%2C%20Redfin%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-housing-market-sales-weather-climate-change-retirement-pandemic-costs-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESimilar%20to%20states%20like%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Texas%20has%20been%20in%20the%20path%20of%20many%20extreme%20weather%20events%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20sending%20home%20insurance%20rates%20skyrocketing.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lendingtree.com%2Finsurance%2Fstate-of-home-insurance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPremiums%20in%20Texas%20have%20soared%2055%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202019%20through%20March%202024%2C%20with%20the%20average%20homeowner%20in%20the%20state%20paying%20%244%2C647%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20LendingTree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20difference%20in%20affordability%20made%20it%20worthwhile%20for%20people%20to%20move%20across%20the%20whole%20country%20and%20start%20a%20new%20life%20in%20Texas.%20But%20now%2C%20because%20home%20prices%20are%20so%20high%2C%20it's%20just%20not%20as%20attractive%2C%26quot%3B%20Fairweather%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20higher%20cost%20of%20living%20broadly%2C%20combined%20with%20a%20weakening%20job%20market%2C%20could%20also%20be%20influencing%20the%20cooling%20interest%20in%20the%20state%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCUURA316SA0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConsumer%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Dallas%2C%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20and%20Arlington%20areas%20have%20risen%2025%25%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FIHLIDXUSTX%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJob%20postings%20based%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Indeed%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20have%20dropped%2028%25%20from%20their%20highs%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Cobb%2C%20an%20East%20Texas%20resident%20who's%20looking%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20state%2C%20said%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20had%20%26quot%3Bblown%20up%26quot%3B%20since%20the%20pandemic.%20He%20and%20his%20wife%20hardly%20save%20anything%2C%20and%20are%20rarely%20even%20able%20to%20dine%20out%20at%20restaurants%20anymore%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20no%20longer%20able%20to%20live%20there%2C%20couldn't%20get%20back%20there%2C%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20get%20jobs%20there%20or%20anything%20else%2C%20so%20they%20just%20pushed%20us%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20Austin.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20basically%20struggling%20to%20afford%20to%20live%20anywhere%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20and%20former%20Texas%20residents%20who%20spoke%20with%20BI%20also%20frequently%20cited%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-texas-political-freedom-property-taxes-housing-costs-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextreme%20heat%20and%20political%20atmosphere%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20key%20motivations%20to%20leave.%20But%20those%20issues%20are%20minor%20relative%20to%20things%20like%20economic%20growth%20and%20housing%20affordability%2C%20Fairweather%20says%2C%20which%20she%20described%20as%20two%20of%20the%20biggest%20factors%20that%20could%20determine%20if%20the%20Texas%20housing%20market%20picks%20back%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoholick%2C%20though%2C%20is%20fairly%20certain%20he'll%20never%20return%20to%20the%20state%20long-term.%20He%20recalled%20turning%20down%20a%20recruiter%20earlier%20this%20year%20for%20a%20job%20that%20would%20double%20his%20current%20salary%2C%20though%20the%20position%20was%20based%20in%20Austin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20not%20stomach%20moving%20back%20there%20for%20any%20price%20tag%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECobb%2C%20who%20hasn't%20moved%20out%20of%20Texas%20yet%2C%20also%20doesn't%20see%20himself%20coming%20back%20once%20he%20leaves.%20His%20only%20problem%20is%20selling%20his%20home%2C%20which%20has%20been%20on%20the%20market%20for%20over%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20made%20a%20decision%20in%20August%20or%20July%20to%20move%2C%20and%20now%20we're%20like%2C%20now%20what%20the%20crap%20we're%20going%20to%20do%3F%20We%20want%20to%20get%20there.%20We're%20tired%20of%20the%20Texas%20heat%2C%20tired%20of%20Texas%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we're%20definitely%20feeling%20stuck%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%