0path%20of%20Federal%20Reserve%20policy%20after%20the%20central%20bank%20said%20it's%20shifted%20focus%20to%20the%20labor%20market%20after%20years%20of%20battling%20inflation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20following%20the%20strong%20payroll%20report%2C%20market%20commentators%20say%20they're%20still%20concerned%20that%20inflation%20may%20not%20be%20completely%20in%20the%20rear-view%20%E2%80%94%20and%20next%20week's%20consumer%20price%20index%20report%20will%20be%20key.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20saw%20an%20astonishing%20254%2C000%20new%20jobs%20added%20last%20month%2C%20smashing%20consensus%20estimates%20of%20147%2C000.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20dropped%20to%204.1%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20economist%20Mohamed%20El-Erian%2C%20this%20permits%20the%20Fed%20to%20once%20again%20devote%20some%20of%20its%20attention%20to%20fighting%20inflation.%20Inflation%20concerns%20took%20a%20back%20seat%20in%20recent%20months%20as%20the%20central%20bank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-cut-explained-inflation-labor-market-conditions-outlook-recession-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshifted%20focus%3C%2Fa%3E%20toward%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%20deteriorating%20labor%20picture.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20September's%20jobs%20report%20crushing%20expectations%2C%20concerns%20may%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-10-04%2Fsummers-says-50-basis-point-cut-in-september-was-a-mistake%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20premature%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20Fed%2C%20it%20means%20push%20back%20much%20harder%20against%20pressure%20from%20the%20markets%20to%20put%20you%20in%20the%20single-mandate%20box%2C%26quot%3B%20El-Erian%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-10-04%2Fel-erian-warns-fed-after-jobs-data-inflation-is-not-dead%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20TV%3C%2Fa%3