t.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeigle%20said%20that%20market%20prices%20tend%20to%20%26quot%3Bfluctuate%20in%20times%20of%20actual%20or%20feared%20supply%20shortages%20as%20traders%20re-price%20the%20value%20of%20an%20increasingly%20scarce%20commodity%20relative%20to%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20noting%20that%20supply%20disruption%20is%20related%20primarily%20to%20two%20factors%3A%20how%20much%20oil%20is%20offline%20and%20for%20how%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Israel%20did%20strike%20Iran's%20oil%2C%20it%20would%20likely%20have%20two%20main%20targets.%20One%20is%20its%20oil%20refiners%2C%20which%20provide%20the%20country%20with%20transportation%20fuels%20and%20gasoline.%20The%20other%20is%20Iran's%20production%20and%20export%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Israel%20hit%20even%20a%20few%20of%20its%20petroleum%20refiners%2C%20it%C2%A0%26quot%3Bcould%20create%20a%20gasoline%20fuel%20shortage%20in%20Iran%2C%26quot%3B%20Seigle%20said.%20But%20that%20wouldn't%20necessarily%20impact%20the%20global%20oil%20supply.%20If%20Israel%20struck%20Iran's%20oil%20production%20and%20export%20facilities%2C%20that%20would%20have%C2%A0%26quot%3Bfar%20greater%20repercussions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20military%20operation%20that%20cuts%20this%20output%20would%20leave%20the%20world%20with%20less%20crude%20supply%2C%20causing%20prices%20to%20rise.%20This%20week%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20markets%20finally%20began%20contemplating%20this%20scenario%3B%20oil%20prices%20have%20increased%20more%20than%205%20percent%20as%20this%20risk%20begins%20to%20be%20'priced%20in%2C'%20Seigle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20has%20weighed%20in%20on%20discussions%20surrounding%20what%20Israel's%20retaliation%20could%20look%20like.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20Biden%20said%20the%20US%20wouldn't%20support%20Israeli%20strikes%20on%20sites%20related%20to%20Iran's%20nuclear%20program.%20Then%2C%20on%20Thursday%2C%20he%20said%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20were%20discussing%20whether%20the%20US%20would%20support%20Israel%20striking%20Iran's%20oil%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHours%20after%20Biden's%20comment%2C%20crude%20oil%20prices%20jumped%205%25.%20The%20National%20Iranian%20Tanker%20Company%20also%20moved%20its%20tankers%20from%20Kharg%20Island's%20oil%20terminal%20in%20apparent%20fear%20of%20an%20imminent%20attack%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FTankerTrackers%2Fstatus%2F1841895357434732660%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETankerTrackers.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20independent%20online%20service%20that%20keeps%20tabs%20on%20the%20movements%20of%20crude%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Biden%20appeared%20to%20backtrack%20on%20his%20earlier%20targeting%20comments%2C%20telling%20reporters%20that%20if%20he%20were%20in%20the%20Israeli's%20shoes%2C%20he%20would%20consider%20alternate%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Joe%20Biden%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f43e670d59cc64f5b01fd2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBiden%20has%20indicated%20there%20are%20conversations%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20about%20whether%20Iran's%20oil%20facilities%20are%20a%20legitimate%20retaliatory%20strike%20option.%3Cp%3EMichael%20M.%20Santiago%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20of%20the%20conflict%20expanding%20is%20high.%20Nicholas%20Carl%2C%20the%20researcher%20manager%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.criticalthreats.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Enterprise%20Institute's%20Critical%20Threats%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20focuses%20on%20Iran%2C%20explained%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bthroughout%20this%20entire%20series%20of%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20there's%20been%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%20risk%20of%20miscalculations%26quot%3B%20for%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20US%20did%20support%20striking%20oil%20facilities%2C%20it%20would%20come%20at%20odds%20with%20Washington's%20stance%20on%20Ukraine%20doing%20the%20same%20thing%20to%20Russia.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-wont-stop-targeting-russias-oil-refineries-will-defy-us-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20urged%20Ukraine%20to%20cease%20its%20attacks%20on%20Russia's%20energy%20infrastructure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20warning%20its%20drone%20strikes%20could%20drive%20up%20global%20oil%20prices%20and%20provoke%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Ukraine%20was%20using%20long-range%20attack%20drones%20to%20strike%20various%20Russian%20oil%20refineries%2C%20terminals%2C%20storage%20facilities%2C%20and%20depots%2C%20intending%20to%20hurt%20its%20production%20capacity.%20Russia%20is%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20energy%20exporters%2C%20although%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20have%20imposed%20hefty%20sanctions%20on%20its%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWashington's%20concerns%20came%20just%20as%20Biden%20began%20pushing%20his%20reelection%20campaign%20and%20before%20his%20historic%20dropout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUS%20policymakers%20and%20politicians%20are%20more%20dedicated%20to%20Israel's%20security%20(and%20to%20showcasing%20this%20dedication)%20than%20they%20are%20to%20Ukraine's%2C%26quot%3B%20Seigle%20said.%20Publicly%2C%20they're%20less%20likely%20to%20rein%20Israel%20in%20from%20those%20ambitions.%20Privately%2C%20though%2C%20Biden%20officials%20are%20%26quot%3Bsurely%20very%20concerned%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20such%20a%20strike%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsrael%20and%20Iran%20hold%20%26quot%3Bmore%20potential%20to%20disrupt%20global%20markets%20and%20send%20prices%20surging%20than%20does%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Seigle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f45eb6e9-e88e-489e-95a4-b2d1c7d08722%5C%22%3EFew%20things%20are%20watched%20more%20closely%20than%20gas%20prices%20ahead%20of%20an%20election%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226865%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kamala%20Harris%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e9ebbbd17aa3c7b2b391a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224577%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202024%20election%20is%20in%20its%20final%20weeks%2C%20and%20the%20Harris%20campaign%20has%20grabbled%20with%20voter%20issues%20related%20to%20the%20economy%20and%20inflation.%3Cp%3EJIM%20WATSON%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Israel%20does%20target%20Iran's%20oil%20industry%2C%20the%202024%20presidential%20election%20could%20be%20rocked%20by%20rising%20oil%20prices%20ahead%20of%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOil%20prices%20had%20notably%20been%20trending%20downwards%20in%20the%20months%20prior%20to%20Iran's%20ballistic%20missile%20attack%20on%20Israel.%20Back%20in%20September%2C%20global%20oil%20prices%20fell%20to%20the%20lowest%20level%20in%20almost%20three%20years%2C%20and%20the%20US%20has%20seen%20a%20historic%20year%20of%20oil%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20prices%20at%20the%20pump%20were%20to%20soar%20in%20response%20to%20upheavals%20abroad%20amid%20domestic%20concerns%20about%20issues%20like%20inflation%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20problem%2C%20as%20it%20has%20been%20historically.%20That%20said%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20changes%20like%20these%20has%20begun%20to%20lessen%20in%20this%20hyperpartisan%20era.%20It%20is%20increasingly%20less%20likely%20for%20a%20president's%20approval%20rating%20to%20swing%20dramatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20Friday%2C%20the%20national%20average%20was%20at%20%243.17%20a%20gallon%2C%20according%20to%20GasBuddy.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20September%2C%20the%20average%20was%20down%20both%20on%20a%20month-to-month%20basis%20and%20on%20a%20year-to-year%20basis.%20Predicting%20gas%20prices%20can%20be%20difficult%2C%20given%20just%20how%20dra